virtual IModel* glr::models::IModelManager::createInstance ( const std::string &  name)
pure virtual

Creates an instance of the model with name 'name'. This model can have animations and animation times set distinctly from other models created with this method.

Parameters
nameThe name of the IModel template you want to create an instance of.
Returns
A pointer to a model object. The model is a copy of the model that was previously loaded with the specified name.

Implemented in glr::models::ModelManager.

virtual void glr::models::IModelManager::destroyInstance ( Id  id)
pure virtual

Destroys the instance of the model with id 'id'. Any pointers or references to this model will become defunct.

If no IModel instance with id 'id' is found, this method does nothing.

Parameters
idThe id of the IModel instance you want to destroy.

Implemented in glr::models::ModelManager.

virtual void glr::models::IModelManager::destroyInstance ( IModel *  model)

Destroys the instance of the IModel 'model'. Any pointers or references to this model will become defunct.

virtual void glr::models::IModelManager::destroyModelTemplate ( Id  id)
pure virtual

Destroys the template of the IModel object with id 'id'. Any pointers or references to this model will become defunct.

Note: Any instances of this model will still be valid.

If no IModel template is found with id 'id', this method does nothing.

Parameters
idThe id of the IModel instance you want to destroy.

virtual IModel* glr::models::IModelManager::getModelTemplate ( Id  id) const
pure virtual

Returns a pointer to an IModel object. This object is the 'template' that is used when creating instances of this model.

Parameters
idThe id of the IModel template you want to get.
Returns
The raw pointer to an IModel object. The caller does not own the pointer - it is managed by the ModelManager.

Implemented in glr::models::ModelManager.
